WEBVTT

00:00:02.780 --> 00:00:05.210
There's always the custom that when a person is

00:00:05.210 --> 00:00:07.540
about to die, they first make a wish and then

00:00:07.540 --> 00:00:08.360
they bury them.

00:00:09.940 --> 00:00:12.800
There was a person who used a wheelchair.

00:00:12.800 --> 00:00:15.980
And when he was about to die, with all his family

00:00:15.980 --> 00:00:18.140
around his bed, he made his wish.

00:00:18.140 --> 00:00:21.320
When I die, I want them to put it inside the coffin.

00:00:23.760 --> 00:00:25.720
And the family granted his wish.

00:00:25.820 --> 00:00:28.640
The day of the funeral arrived, and the family.

00:00:28.640 --> 00:00:30.466
Buried him with his wheelchair.

00:00:31.420 --> 00:00:33.680
The second person was blind, and when he was

00:00:33.680 --> 00:00:35.990
about to die, with all his family around his

00:00:35.990 --> 00:00:37.100
bed, he made his wish.

00:00:37.100 --> 00:00:38.930
I want that when I die, please.

00:00:38.930 --> 00:00:40.420
And the family granted it.

00:00:40.420 --> 00:00:42.160
When he died, at the funeral,

00:00:42.160 --> 00:00:45.170
they buried the blind person and placed his cane

00:00:45.170 --> 00:00:46.326
inside the coffin.

00:00:47.620 --> 00:00:49.850
And the third was an oral deaf person,

00:00:49.850 --> 00:00:52.710
and when he was about to die with all his family,

00:00:52.710 --> 00:00:53.700
he made his wish.

00:00:53.700 --> 00:00:55.600
I wish, and his family granted it.

00:00:55.600 --> 00:00:57.260
When they buried him, they put the

00:00:57.260 --> 00:00:59.070
cochlear implant and the hearing aid

00:00:59.070 --> 00:00:59.983
inside the coffin.

00:01:01.340 --> 00:01:03.500
Then came a signing deaf person, and when

00:01:03.500 --> 00:01:05.610
he was about to die, he made his wish,

00:01:05.610 --> 00:01:06.620
and they granted it.

00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:08.190
When the burial was held,

00:01:08.190 --> 00:01:11.020
they brought the live interpreter in handcuffs

00:01:11.020 --> 00:01:13.120
and buried her with the deaf person.
